quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  47,10,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those before them? God annihilated them, and a similar fate awaits the disbelievers"
  47,11,This is because God is the Patron of the believers while the disbelievers have no patron
  47,12,"Surely God will admit those who believe and do good into Gardens under which rivers flow. As for the disbelievers, they enjoy themselves and feed like cattle.Ā But the Fire will be their home"
  47,13,"Ė¹Imagine, O Prophet,Ėŗ how many societies We destroyed that were far superior in might than your societyāwhich drove you outāand there was none to help them"
  47,14,Can those Ė¹believersĖŗ who stand on clear proof from their Lord be like those whose evil deeds are made appealing to them and Ė¹onlyĖŗ follow their desires
  47,15,"The description of the Paradise promised to the righteous is that in it are rivers of fresh water, rivers of milk that never changes in taste, rivers of wine delicious to drink, and rivers of pure honey. There they will Ė¹alsoĖŗ have all kinds of fruit, and forgiveness from their Lord. Ė¹Can they beĖŗ like those who will stay in the Fire forever, left to drink boiling water that will tear apart their insides"
  47,16,"There are some of them who listen to you Ė¹O ProphetĖŗ, but when they depart from you, they say Ė¹mockinglyĖŗ to those Ė¹believersĖŗ gifted with knowledge, āWhat did he just say?ā These are the ones whose hearts God has sealed and who Ė¹onlyĖŗ follow their desires"
  47,17,"As for those who are Ė¹rightlyĖŗ guided, He increases them in guidance and blesses them with righteousness"
  47,18,"Are they only waiting for the Hour to take them by surprise? Yet Ė¹some ofĖŗ its signs have already come.Ā Once it actually befalls them, will it not be too late to be mindful"
  47,19,"So, know Ė¹well, O Prophet,Ėŗ that there is no god Ė¹worthy of worshipĖŗ except God. And seek forgiveness for your shortcomingsĀ and for Ė¹the sins ofĖŗ the believing men and women. For God Ė¹fullyĖŗ knows your movements and places of rest Ė¹O peopleĖŗ"
  47,20,"And the believers say, āIf only a sĆ»rahĀ was revealed Ė¹allowing self-defenceĖŗ!ā Yet when a precise sĆ»rahĀ is revealed, in which fighting is Ė¹explicitlyĖŗ mentioned, you see those with sickness in their hearts staring at you like someone in the throes of death. It would have been better for them"
  47,21,"to obey and speak rightly. Then when fighting was ordained, it surely would have been better for them if they were true to God"
  47,22,"Now if you Ė¹hypocritesĖŗ turn away, perhaps you would then spread corruption throughout the land and sever your Ė¹ties ofĖŗ kinship"
  47,23,"These are the ones who God has condemned, deafening them and blinding their eyes"
  47,24,Do they not then reflect on the Quran? Or are there locks upon their hearts
  47,25,"Indeed, those who relapse Ė¹into disbeliefĖŗ after Ė¹trueĖŗ guidance has become clear to them, Ė¹it isĖŗ Satan Ė¹thatĖŗ has tempted them, luring them with false hopes"
  47,26,"That is because they said Ė¹privatelyĖŗ to those who Ė¹alsoĖŗ detest what God has revealed, āWe will obey you in some matters.āĀ But God Ė¹fullyĖŗ knows what they are hiding"
  47,27,"Then how Ė¹horribleĖŗ will it be when the angels take their souls, beating their faces and backs"
  47,28,"This is because they follow whatever displeases God and hate whatever pleases Him, so He has rendered their deeds void"
  47,29,Or do those with sickness in their hearts think that God will not Ė¹be able toĖŗ expose their malice
  47,30,"Had We willed, We could have truly shown them to you Ė¹O ProphetĖŗ, and you would have certainly recognized them by their appearance. But you will surely recognize them by their tone of speech. And God Ė¹fullyĖŗ knows your doings Ė¹O peopleĖŗ"
  47,31,"We will certainly test you Ė¹believersĖŗ until We prove those of you who Ė¹trulyĖŗ struggle Ė¹in Godās causeĖŗ and remain steadfast, and reveal how you conduct yourselves"
  47,32,"Indeed, those who disbelieve, hinder Ė¹othersĖŗ from the Way of God, and defy the Messenger after Ė¹trueĖŗ guidance has become clear to them; they will not harm God in the least, but He will render their deeds void"